Here’s how to record your screen depending on your platform — super quick guide:

🖥️ Mac (QuickTime built-in)

  1. Press Cmd + Shift + 5

  2. Select “Record Entire Screen” or drag to record a portion

  3. Hit “Record”

  4. Click stop in the menu bar when you’re done
    🔁 Video saves to Desktop by default

💻 Windows (Xbox Game Bar)

  1. Press Win + G to open Game Bar

  2. Click the Record button (or Win + Alt + R)

  3. Do your demo

  4. Hit stop or press Win + Alt + R again
    🔁 File saved in Videos > Captures

🧠 Pro Tip: Want voice too?

Yes — you can absolutely move the screen while recording!

Here's how it works:

🔹 Mac

  • If you select “Record Selected Portion” (Cmd + Shift + 5), you can:

    • Resize or move the recording area before hitting record.

    • Once recording starts, you can still scroll, click, hover, and navigate pages freely — all movements are captured.

🔹 Windows (Xbox Game Bar)

  • It records the active window or app.

    • You can interact, scroll, and switch tabs within that app while recording.

    • If you change apps, the recording may pause unless you're screen recording the whole display (some tools allow that).

Prompt for Claude: Build n8n Workflow for '10 Pic Push' (Content Alchemist Sub-Product)

You're acting as an AI automation engineer. I want you to generate a fully modular n8n workflow that powers a product called "10 Pic Push" — a free, low-pressure onboarding and content transformation experience for social creators. The user provides up to 10 images, answers a few fun branding questions, and receives a preview of what their personal brand and content output could look like. No posting is done — this is purely a brand discovery and content simulation tool.

🎯 Product Overview:

10 Pic Push is an automated AI-powered experience targeted at the "EDGE" market — those who want to build a presence online but haven’t started or feel overwhelmed. The goal is to give them an exciting, judgment-free look at what their brand could be.

They upload 2–10 photos + answer a short quiz → your workflow returns:

  • A short brand description / "About You"

  • 3 short-form content ideas (caption + script)

  • 2 carousel content outlines (headlines + callouts)

  • 3 post hook lines

  • All styled to match the user’s aesthetic, tone, and goals

📥 Workflow Inputs:

  • 2–10 user-uploaded images (Firebase or UploadThing ref paths)

  • User answers from onboarding quiz:

    • Tone (text + dropdown selection)

    • Vibes (array of chips: bold, raw, elegant, etc.)

    • Metaphor/location: e.g., "My brand is a neon skate park"

    • Audience type (text)

    • Sample copy (optional)

🧠 Your Task:

Design an n8n JSON workflow with the following characteristics:

  1. Modular — Each section (brand voice, short content, carousels) should be a separate function or GPT node block

  2. Creatively Flexible — Feel free to improve the output quality or add creative nodes Claude might think improve realism, emotional resonance, or UX value

  3. Bookaphi-Aware — Incorporate logic for breaking down inputs into structured format before generating content. Use tone + metaphor + example copy to guide generation.

  4. Firebase Integration — Store the user profile & generated content bundle in a Firebase 10PicResults/ collection with timestamp, user ID (if present), and file refs

  5. Final Output JSON Format should be structured for display in a mobile carousel preview — each content item should include:

    • type (e.g., reel, post, carousel)

    • title / headline

    • caption or script

    • CTA or suggested hashtags (if relevant)

🛠️ Nodes to Include (Minimum):

  • Webhook Trigger

  • Image Ref Collector (input parser)

  • User Profile Parser (based on quiz)

  • Brand Voice Builder (GPT node)

  • Content Generator Node 1: Reels x3

  • Content Generator Node 2: Carousels x2

  • Content Generator Node 3: Hooks x3

  • Output Formatter (JSON node)

  • Firebase Writer (Save all content + input refs)

✨ Optional Enhancements (Up to Claude):

  • Use vision model or API to extract aesthetic keywords from images

  • Add safety check node (e.g., NSFW or banned words filter)

  • Suggest emoji, tone, or time-of-day posting guidance

  • Return short affirmation or encouragement message from "The Alchemist"

Please return:

  • A complete n8n-compatible JSON workflow (or modular logic to be converted)

  • Any custom prompt blocks used for the GPT/Claude nodes

  • Explanation of any extra creative decisions you made

This is going to be deployed as the back-end engine for a product experience that introduces creators to their brand in a personalized, imaginative way — feel free to surprise, elevate, and inspire.
